Subject: Re: [T2] Calibrating the Fuel Gauge

David Schwarze wrote:
> Your instrument cluster should have a small box attached behind the 
> fuel gauge with a wire coming from it.  If you're lucky, this box will 
> have a very small set screw in it (I've seen some with and some 
> without).  You will probably need a jeweler's screwdriver to turn it.  
> This seems to adjust the span on the gauge but if I remember correctly 
> it adjusts the low and high side of the gauge simultaneously.  You may 
> have to experiment with it or perhaps someone else here knows more 
> about it than I do and can explain.
There are two screws - one for the high adjustment and one for the low 
adjustment.  Just don't make the same mistake that I did and take the 
sender out and hold it at full.  The tank never actually pushes the 
sender that high so my tank never reads full now :)

Mike
